<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10474</anchor> <rss>erct-0028.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0028</addr>  <route>erct-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositional truncation</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex> we have a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex> equipped with a unit map <tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">propositions</link> <tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</tex>, any function <tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> extends to a function <tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</tex>.</p><p>When we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>, we will say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10475</anchor> <rss>erct-003R.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003R</addr>  <route>erct-003R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › propositional truncation and existence</title> <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10476</anchor> <rss>erct-0028.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0028</addr>  <route>erct-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositional truncation</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex> we have a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex> equipped with a unit map <tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">propositions</link> <tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</tex>, any function <tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> extends to a function <tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</tex>.</p><p>When we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>, we will say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10477</anchor> <rss>erct-002A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr>  <route>erct-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10478</anchor> <rss>erct-0029.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr>  <route>erct-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10479</anchor> <rss>erct-003F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003F</addr>  <route>erct-003F.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Bijection</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003F.agda" type="external">erct-003F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>bijective</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10480</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractible type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10481</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10482</anchor> <rss>erct-002X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr>  <route>erct-002X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10483</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002X</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10484</anchor> <rss>erct-002Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Y</addr>  <route>erct-002Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Y.agda" type="external">erct-002Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10485</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002Y</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>b:B</tex>, we must check that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link>; because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> to observe that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <em>inhabited</em> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>